    {
      "logical_unit_id": "MD12056_lu15",
      "document_id": "MD12056",
      "title": "1.3.2 Wrong reporting",
      "text": "1.3.2 Wrong reporting\nPenal interest will be levied in respect of cases of wrong reporting in the same manner\ntill the date of receipt of corrected advice by Reserve Bank. As debits/credits to banks'\ncurrent accounts are raised on the basis of the transactions reported by the currency\nchests, penal interest will invariably be levied in all cases of wrong reporting by the\ncurrency chests. It is expected that currency chests would ensure the correctness of\nfigures reported on the CyM - CC portal. Particular care should be taken to ensure that\nremittances of fresh notes/notes to the currency chests are not reported as 'deposit'\ntransactions on the portal.",
      "node_type": "clause",
      "level": 5,
      "page_range": [
        2
      ],
      "hierarchy_node_ids": [
