    {
      "logical_unit_id": "MD12056_lu27",
      "document_id": "MD12056",
      "title": "4.1 As the sole criterion for levy of penal interest for delayed reporting is the number of",
      "text": "4.1 As the sole criterion for levy of penal interest for delayed reporting is the number of\ndays of delay, there should ordinarily be no occasion for banks to request for\nreconsideration of the Reserve Bank's decision in individual cases. However,\nrepresentations, if any, on account of genuine difficulties faced by chests especially in\nhilly/remote areas and those affected by natural calamities, etc., may be made to the\nIssue Office concerned through the Head / Controlling office of the bank concerned\nwithin a month from the date of debit of the bank concerned.",
